HEADWORD: Decurrent
<hw>De*cur"rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>decurrens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>decurrere</ets>
to run down; <ets>de-</ets> + <ets>currere</ets> to run: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧current</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Extending
downward; -- said of a leaf whose base extends downward and forms a wing
along the stem.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>De*cur"rent*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decursion</ent>⟦br⟧
